Ruby "Getting Started" Kata
===========================


- Quick kata to get used to (some of) the basics of Ruby.


- Create Project
- Creating First Test (http://www.ruby-doc.org/stdlib/libdoc/test/unit/rdoc/classes/Test/Unit.html)
    - Create PercentMax Test for "0%".
- Class Creation
    - Create PercentMax
    - See Test Fail
    - Override/Define "to_s" and Get Test Passing
- Add Tests for:
    - 50%
    - 100%
    - 100% (>100)
    - 0% (<0)
- Add Tests for Formatting
    - 10.11 = 10.11%
    - 10.115 = 10.11%
    - 60.8723 = 60.87%
    - 0.001 = 0%
    - 100.755 = 100%
- Add Tests for Invalid Input
    - Non-Numeric String